WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.700
Equation 11 asks for query and key transformations whose inner product depends on the relative position m minus n.

00:04.700 --> 00:10.800
Equations 14 through 16 rotate query and key vectors by their positions. Their inner product contains the relative rotation R sub n minus m.

00:10.800 --> 00:16.100
The official implementation constructs the perpendicular companion, applies cosine and sine elementwise, and then uses the ordinary attention dot product.
